=3D one of the most reliable wealth transfer mechanisms ever invented. Don=
=E2=80=99t be the transferor. BE A COMPOUNDER</p></blockquote><p style=3D"m=
argin:10px 0">I=E2=80=99ve had so many offers over the years to get into Sp=
aceX, Anduril, xAI, and similar private names. The terms were almost always=
 the same toxic cocktail: 2=E2=80=932.5% management fee, 20% profit share, =
and a 3-to-5-year lockup (sometimes longer). Let me walk you thru why IMHO =
this is the kiss of death.  PS Got the same terms this week multiple times =
at the all in liquidity event in Yountville. </p><h2>The DEAL</h2><p style=
=3D"margin:10px 0">Imagine at At age 25 you hand a hedge fund manager $100,=
000. He delivers a 7% average annual gross return.</p><p style=3D"margin:10=
px 0">Add the standard =E2=80=9C2 and 20=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94 2% management f=
ee + 20% performance fee =E2=80=94 and the outcome is brutal.</p><p style=
=3D"margin:10px 0">After 40 years (age 65):</p><ul><li><p style=3D"margin:1=
0px 0"><strong>No fees</strong>: Your $100K grows to <strong>~$1,497,446</s=
trong></p></li><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0"><strong>After 2/20 fees</stro=
ng> (modeled correctly year-by-year): You end up with only <strong>~$480,10=
2</strong></p></li></ul><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">That=E2=80=99s more than=
 <strong>$1 million</strong> extracted in fees from a single $100K account.=
 The managers and their partners make millions on your back while you take =
all the risk. YOU LOSE, THEY WIN</p><h2>Why I never took the so called "DEA=
L"</h2><ol><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">I don=E2=80=99t like locking my m=
oney up =E2=80=94 not even for a day. Because I could be dead in three year=
s. </p></li><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Second I understand how even a q=
uiet 2% fee can destroy your returns - kinda like taxes</p></li><li><p styl=
e=3D"margin:10px 0">I know I can outperform hedge funds. </p></li></ol><h2>=
The Rule: </h2><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Never voluntarily hand your capit=
al to a vehicle that charges high fees <em>and</em> locks it up for years. =
Liquidity is freedom. In most cases you=E2=80=99re far better off owning hi=
gh-conviction assets directly in public markets where you control your mone=
y every single day and pay little to nothing in fees and even sell calls on=
 top. </p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0"></p><p></p></div></td></tr>
